result.execSummary:
The defendant Kyle N DeMelle was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: To pay the costs of the action. Costs have been paid in full from cash bond posted.

Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol.  Not to possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription and then only take in the amount and frequency prescribed.  Not to possess or use any drug paraphernalia.

Complete any counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments, including AODA assessment, as appropriate resulting from the Department's COMPAS assessment. Defendant can petition for early termination of probation after 12 months upon completion of all conditions of probation and with recommendation of Dept. of Corrections.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Kyle N DeMelle in court with attorney Shane Laughton Brabazon.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Ct. 1.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty of Ct. 1. Court dismisses Ct. 2 but reads in for sentencing. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.

State will file an Information on Tuesday, 4/19/16 with the same charges as shown in the criminal complaint. Assuming the Information mirrors the criminal complaint, Defense waives reading of Information and enters not guilty plea.  Atty Brabazon anticipates a possible plea at next hearing. requests a date in mid May. Bond remains as is.

Defendant Kyle N DeMelle in court with attorney Shane Laughton Brabazon.  Kevin Charles Greene appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense waives right to Prelim. Court questions defendant on waiver. Court finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver and binds over for trial. Court finds probable cause for bindover.  Status conference scheduled for May 16, 2016 at 04:00 pm.
from Aaron Carmody and Pamela DeMelle on defendants behalf.

Defendant Kyle N DeMelle in court.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Copy of Complaint given to Defendant in Court.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel, right to preliminary hearing.   Court adjourns matter to give defendant time to talk to Atty Brabazon about this case. Bond remains in effect.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for April 18, 2016 at 03:45 pm.
No violent contact with C.R.    Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol.  To be fingerprinted and photographed before leaving the Justice Center.
